title: For Sale:  1529 rds. 8mm Mauser
postcontent: I have 1,529 rounds (laid out, counted, and pictured) of persian 8mm Mauser ammunition. This ammo is live and should be treated as such, however, because of its age (~1930s) it is best suited as components for reloading purposes. I no longer reload rifle rounds because I just don't have the time or motivation. I would pull the bullets, salvage the powder, de-prime the cases, and sell the brass to a scrap yard. This is a much cheaper way to reload for 8mm surplus rifles.Due to mass low baller spam I am setting the price to ~0.13 per round for a fixed price of $200 for all 1,529 rounds and cash only. The cheapest 8mm projectiles on the market currently are PPU at ~0.25 per bullet. At 0.13 per round you are getting a projectile, powder load, and brass to trade to a scrap yard for some money back or convert to boxer primers. You won't find 8mm components this cheap anywhere else, ever.If your email has anything other than "I'll take it" it's going straight to the trash folder, spammers will be blocked so don't waste your time. Just need to see an Arizona ID and you're good to go.
